<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-15T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-15T22:00:00-05:00" n="839" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/7–1648: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Manila</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-16T11:00:00+08:00">July
                                        16, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1305, Contents of Depcirtel July 10, 1 p. m. [<hi rend="italic">a.
                                    m.</hi>], concerning action to be taken in Korea relative
                                problem recognition Korean Government to be formed as result May 10
                                elections were discussed yesterday with President Quirino. He stated
                                “My government is a member of <gloss target="#t_UNTCOK1">UNTCOK</gloss> and therefore I feel that measures decided upon
                                by the Commission should be supported. I see no objection to the
                                plan of action contemplated by the US soon after the formation of
                                the new Korean Government”.</p>
                            <p>The latter part of the foregoing statement refers to paragraph
                                numbered 6 Depcirtel July 10, 1 p. m. [<hi rend="italic">a. m.</hi>]
                                which I had just read to him verbatim.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockett</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>